      "fever (38-40\u00b0C in ~50% \u2014 from cytokine-driven inflammation, not always infection)",
      "neutrophilic leukocytosis (WBC often 10,000-20,000/\u00b5L despite no infection)",
      "right upper quadrant pain or fullness",
      "hepatic encephalopathy in severe cases (most reliable indicator of severity)"
    ],
    "signs": [
      "acute or subacute onset jaundice after heavy alcohol use",
      "tender hepatomegaly (liver may be palpable 4-6 cm below costal margin)",
      "anorexia, nausea, vomiting, and significant weight loss",
      "stigmata of chronic liver disease: spider angiomata, palmar erythema, asterixis",
      "ascites and peripheral edema in severe disease"
    ],
